cs.GT, cs.IR, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.MA 

This paper is likely to belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) category as it proposes a mechanism for maximizing social welfare in an adversarial setting. It also involves the optimization of bids and assignments, which could fall under Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Data Structures (cs.DS) categories. The use of optimization techniques and convergence analysis suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) categories.
